<!DOCTYPE document PUBLIC "-//APACHE//DTD Documentation V1.2//EN" "http://forrest.apache.org/dtd/document-v12.dtd">
<document>
	<header>
		<title>Dependencies</title>
	</header>
	<body>
		<p>
			CILib is quite a comprehensive framework, but gets support from different open-source frameworks. The following
			libraries are required to build and test CILib.
		</p>
		
		<table>
			<tr>
				<th>Library</th>
				<th>Version</th>
				<th>License</th>
				<th>Description</th>
			</tr>
			<tr>
				<td><link href="http://jakarta.apache.org/commons/logging/">commons-logging</link></td>
				<td>1.0.4</td>
				<td>ASL</td>
				<td>Logging framework that acts as a wrapper around JDK 1.4 logging, Log4J or others.</td>
			</tr>
			<tr>
				<td><link href="http://www.junit.org">junit</link></td>
				<td>4.0</td>
				<td>CPL</td>
				<td>Unit Testing framework used for regression testing.</td>
			</tr>
			<tr>
				<td><link href="http://xerces.apache.org/xerces2-j/">Xerces-J</link></td>
				<td>2.8.0</td>
				<td>ASF</td>
				<td>XML library used for parsing of XML documents</td>
			</tr>
		</table>
		
		
		<note>
			CILib source is completely based on the language spec of JDK 1.5 / 5.0. CILib will <strong>not compile</strong> with a JDK &lt;= 1.4.2
		</note>
	</body>	
</document>
